I ran into this thread while getting a 2019 outreach bot up and running. The links above appear dead, but if anyone else is looking for the 2019 image, CSA-USB-Tool here has a working link to download the 2019 update suite (FRCUpdateSuite_2019.2.0.zip). And if you just want the roboRIO image, you can run Distributions\FRC Utilities\Products\FRC_Utilities\FRC_U00\FRC_Utilities.msi directly, which installs the image to C:\Program Files (x86)\National Instruments\LabVIEW 2018\project\roboRIO Tool\FRC Images\FRC_roboRIO_2019_v14.zip (which you can use in the 2022 roboRIO imaging tool if you copy it into the 2022 images folder). It even works under Wine with msiexec /i FRC_Utilities.msi

Disclaimer: I haven’t tested this on a system that already had NI/FRC tools installed, so I may be unaware of some side effects of this installer, but it appears to just be copying some static files.
